<br>
For melees just sort them into tanks / dmg.  Bards = utility (you're lacking those as a prerequisite btw, can't beat a bard for resists, grp them with the ma/sa/clrs first and then if you can probably the dmg grps next)<br>
<br>
Warriors, pallies, sks = tanks, just need MA/SA as warriors, the rest *can* be pallies or sk's<br>
<br>
Rogue, monk, ranger = dmg, and in that order but given that positioning and aggro control  probably won't be too great if it's a ugod raid the rogue's dps edge might be lost.   Those 3 classes are the meat and gravy of melee dmg and are for the most part interchangable and very stackable.<br>
<br>
For pulling you can get by with one monk and let the SA go to tag if the monk is good.  A 2nd FDable tagger to bring the mobs in would be ideal though.  Wouldn't let waiting on a 3rd hold you up.  After the 1st monk an SK should be able to fill in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ugreatdark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>greatdark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#ff9933>Drinalien</font></span><br>  Posts: 272<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/17/02 4:27:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3863.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Things need to change! ( dragon raid ideas )</span><hr size=1> Sorry not the biggest bard fan BUT 1 or 2 i guess cant hurt.<br>
